				<td colspan="2"><hr /></td>
			</tr>
			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">By far, Improved Reclaim is our most powerful ability.  It's the only class ability that takes a mere 3 points to max, yet it can totally change game dynamics solo and grouped.
<br />

<br />
I understand that not everyone chains pets, but you can't deny the impact this skill has on the chainers.  Being able to group magicians together and kill xp mobs yet have no need for clarity, slows, snare, root, or heals is a huge impact for 3 little AA points.
<br />

<br />
In comparison, Pet Discipline (6 AA points) has a minimal impact on the (experience grind) game until you start xp hunting mobs that enrage.  Even then big nukes can help compensate for not having the skill. (The skill is awesome though, and well worth the 6 points invested.)
<br />

<br />
Can you compare a single use mana free pet heal (Mend Companion, 5 points) to a skill that lets you resummon an unlimited number of pets in battle and even GAIN mana doing it?
<br />

<br />
I am not saying everyone should get on the IR bandwagon, but give the skill its due.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
