			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Not that I'm saying this is the best path, but here's how I did AA's:
<br />

<br />
SCM 3
<br />
SCF 3
<br />
HoE 3
<br />
FOM 1
<br />
Frenzied Burnout
<br />
Pet Discipline
<br />
CA2 (working on 3 and LR+)
<br />

<br />
There were a few other AA's I sprinkled through that list (elemental forms, etc.) but those were the ones I really thought were worthwhile.
<br />

<br />
Spell Casting Mastery is by far the best thing any caster can get in my opinion, so I'd definately max it out ASAP.  Spell Casting Fury just adds a little random damage here and there, with Fury of Magic adding a bit more chance.  
<br />

<br />
Host of the Elements I REALLY like.  If the pets didn't have so much push, it would be great.  But the average 180 DPS for 30 seconds added every 20 minutes isn't too bad, plus it's great for wowing the crowds ;-)
<br />

<br />
Frenzied Burnout is mostly just one of those show-off AA's, but I find it works really well using charmed pets (in BoT).  Pet discipline is another must have, even with the new pet aggro rules (a lot of people advised me against this AA for some reason, but I'm very glad I spent points for it).  
<br />

<br />
Combat Avoidance I can't say much about, since I don't have enough to really notice anything.  I've seen a mage friend literally tank mobs in PoValor (he had 6k hp's helping in that and only one mob on him, but still impressed me nonetheless) with a cleric keeping him alive.  So I'm guessing LR5 is pretty good for keeping us alive in case we do happen to get some aggro.
<br />

<br />
I also have Improved Reclaim Energy, but I've heard all sorts of views over whether that was a good way to spend points.  I find it useful to reclaim nearly dead pets for nearly full mana cost, but have been told I'll never be able to canni pet "well".<br />_________________<br />-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=994568" taret=_blank>Impresario Sedenten Grey</a>
<br />
Maestro of Firiona Vie
<br />
<a href="http://www.fnfguild.com"><i>Fire and Fury</i></a>
<br />

<br />
-<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=222062" taret=_blank>Sage Booperbustle Tinkermeister</a>
<br />
Arch Convoker of Solusek Ro
<br />
<a href="http://www.furiouspantaloons.org"><i>Furious Pantaloons</i></a></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
